<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span data-colorid=3D"argcu7mdlv">=
Document.IsChangeRequest</span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">true/false</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span data-colorid=3D"crewafwp20">=
 <span data-colorid=3D"iyisywwijk">Document.IsChangeRequest =3D false Add t=
his to any requisition workflow activities that should only be evaluated fo=
r regular requisitions. You may have a lot of rules to modify by adding and=
 &amp;&amp; to the logic. example: Document.<span>GetNumberOfPOs &gt; 1 &am=
p;&amp; Document.IsChangeRequest =3D</span> false. That rule would route an=
y requistion that would split into multiple POs and is not a change request=
. Another example might be the requisition export to an ERP system or a dat=
awarehouse. Prevent the export of change requests to an ERP system by addin=
g this object to a rule in the PR export activitiy. Any steps/activities th=
at should only be used for change requests, then add this rule <span data-c=
olorid=3D"zxfmqu5wag">Document.IsChangeRequest =3D true. Example: (<span>Do=
cument.IsChangeRequest=3D True &amp;&amp; Docline.CommodityCode in </span> =
</span> </span> </span>{20001,20002,5000})<span data-colorid=3D"vj5cic62k2"=
> Just remember to use your parenthesis and or brackets for segmenting the =
logic.</span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">17.3</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">X</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Document.HasChangeRequestTotalDiff=
erence</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">&nbsp;<span>&gt; or &lt; decimal</=
span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">[Document.HasChangeRequestTotalDif=
ference &gt;=3D 100] Use this kind of rule to route a change request in PR =
workflow based on the grand total monetary difference between the original =
PO and the change request.</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">18.1</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">X</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Document.ChangeRequestPercentageDi=
fference</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>&gt; or &lt; decimal</span><=
/td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Use this object to route Change Requests based on grand total percentage=
 difference from their PO. This is based on document total including any ta=
x, shipping and handling.</p>
<p>Example: Document.ChangeRequestPercentageDifference&gt;=3D10<br>
Will stop any CR that will increase the PO total by 10% or greater.</p></td=
>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">18.2</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">X</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">IsBudgetExceeded</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>true/false</span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Checks PR against matching budget =
remainder. <span>Used with new Budget Manager license. </span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">19.1</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Document.ChangeRequestSubtotalDiff=
erence</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>&gt; or &lt; decimal</span><=
/td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">[Document.ChangeRequestSubtotalDif=
ference&gt;=3D 100] Use this kind of rule to route a change request in PR w=
orkflow based on the monetary difference between the original open PO line =
subtotal and the change request subtotal.&nbsp; Open PO line subtotal is de=
fined as the amount left on the line that has not been invoiced.&nbsp; Tax,=
 shipping and handling is not included in this calculation.</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">21.2</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">X</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Document.ChangeRequestSubtotalPerc=
entageDifference</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>&gt; or &lt; decimal</span><=
/td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Use this object to route Change Requests based on percentage difference =
from their PO line subtotal.&nbsp;Open PO line subtotal is defined as the a=
mount left on the line that has not been invoiced.&nbsp; Tax, shipping and =
handling is not included in this calculation.</p>
<p>Example: Document.ChangeRequestSubtotalPercentageDifference&gt;=3D10<br>
Will stop any CR that will increase the PO line subtotal by 10% or greater.=
</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">21.2</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">X</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Document.ChangeRequestAllLinesCanc=
eled</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>true/false</span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span data-colorid=3D"rdaobrvszx">=
This rule will check that the requisition is a change request and that all =
lines in that change request are canceled.&nbsp; This will cause the relate=
d PO to have all of its lines canceled once the change request completes.</=
span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">21.2</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">X</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Document.ContractItemQuantityExcee=
ded</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">true/false</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Returns true if at least one Contr=
act Non-Catalog Item line on the document contains a quantity that exceeds =
the allowable Contracted Quantity for that item, when considering the curre=
nt Total Purchased Quantity of the item added to the proposed line quantity=
, if and only if the item is marked to "Enforce Contracted Quantity". Contr=
acted Quantity, Total Purchased Quantity, and Enforce Contracted Quantity a=
re all new 21.2 attributes on Contract Non-Catalog Items.</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">21.2</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">IsBudgetDateRangeClosed</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">true/false</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Returns true if any line in the tr=
ansaction is associated with a Budget Date Range that is Closed.</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">22.1</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>Has Inactive Owner</span></t=
d>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">true/false</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>(</span>Document.HasInactive=
Owner =3D true<span>) will evaluate to true when the requisition owner is I=
nactive </span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">22.3</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>X</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Document.OriginalSubmitter</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">string</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Returns a string containing the username of the person who is the origin=
al submitter of a requisition.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<p>Document.OriginalSubmitter !=3D jdoe&nbsp;</p>
<p>Document.OriginalSubmitter =3D=3D Submitter.UserName</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">23.1</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">X</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Document.CreatedByIntakeRequest</t=
d>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">true/false</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Returns true if the PR was created=
 from an Intake / Orchestration Request Form</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">25.2</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">X</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
