<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>IsNotValid()</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>true/false</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This function was created primarily to validate POs that are imported an=
d thus haven't already been validated interactively in the Spend Director a=
pplication. <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline">
There are several situations that can result in an imported PO to be consid=
ered "IsNotValid". One of them is mixed orders (i.e. non-catalog forms and =
catalog items on one PO to cXML suppliers that can't accept them). <br clas=
s=3D"atl-forced-newline">
Another is POs that have "empty" distribution methods (i.e. no distribution=
 methods set up for the supplier). <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline">
Another is a PO containing a non-catalog form for a cXML-enabled supplier t=
hat doesn't accept cXML forms. This is regardless of whether the PO is mixe=
d or not. In addition, the secondary delivery method is not evaluated in wo=
rkflow... this is used during the PR creation process online in the Spend D=
irector application.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>5.4</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>HasInvalidDistribution()</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>true/false</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This is an entry rule to capture POs without external distribution or in=
valid distribution. This is only an entry rule and does not make the docume=
nt invalid. That means the document can still be approved without distribut=
ion, however, that will result in the distribution step not completing. <br=
 class=3D"atl-forced-newline">
The rule only applies to PO document.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>8.3</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
