<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue2">Attribut=
e/Function</span></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue2">Returns<=
/span></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue2">Meaning<=
/span></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-blue2">Availabi=
lity</span></th>
<th colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-b=
lue2">Available in ADW</span></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>isESignature</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>true/false</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-red2">The rule <strong>isESignature</st=
rong> is only intended to be used on the <em><strong>ESignature Setup</stro=
ng></em> workflow step</span>. This rule determines if the user needs to ma=
nually configure the signature blocks in the ESignature application (by sel=
ecting "Launch ESignature"). The only scenario where this will be <em>TRUE<=
/em> is if the contract is using eSignature and the signature blocks will b=
e <em>manually </em>configured in the eSignature application.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The rule will evaluate to:&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>TRUE if the contract header field&nbsp;<em>Use for eSignature</em>&nbsp=
;=3D YES&nbsp;<strong>AND</strong>&nbsp;the field&nbsp;<em>Placement of Sig=
nature Block Fields</em>&nbsp;=3D Manual</li>
<li>FALSE&nbsp;if the contract header field&nbsp;<em>Use for eSignature</em=
>&nbsp;=3D YES&nbsp;<strong>AND</strong>&nbsp;the field&nbsp;<em>Placement =
of Signature Block Fields</em>&nbsp;=3D Automatic</li>
<li>FALSE if the contract header field&nbsp;<em>Use for eSignature</em>&nbs=
p;=3D NO</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>15.2</p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>X</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> This rule in ADW will ignore the&nbsp;<em>Placeme=
nt of Signature Blocks</em> field setting and will return TRUE if the&nbsp;=
<em>Use for eSignature&nbsp;</em>field is "Yes" and FALSE if the field is "=
No"</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">isSalesforceContract</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>true/false</span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Was the contract created from the =
Salesforce integration?</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">16.1</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">ContractSubmitterApprover</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span>This is not an entry "rule", but rather a <em><strong>Folder Selec=
tion Rule</strong></em><em> </em>type that can be used to automatically ass=
ign the <em>user who submitted the Contract into workflow</em> as the appro=
ver for this Activity. A folder will automatically be created and the submi=
tter will automatically be assigned as the approver.</span></p>
<p><span>Here's an example how that would look like in the XML: </span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">&lt;Acti=
vity&nbsp;name=3D"WF Submitter Approval"&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;ActivityType&gt;manual&lt;/ActivityType&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;StepRef&nbsp;name=3D"WF Submitter Approval"&nbsp;/&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[true]]&gt;&lt;/Rule&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;ContractSubmitterApprover&lt;/Folder=
SelectionRule&gt;
&lt;/Activity&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">17.1</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">CreatedByIntakeRequest</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">true/false</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Returns true if the Contract was c=
reated from an Intake / Orchestration Request Form</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">25.2</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">X</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
