<td class=3D"confluenceTd">true/false</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Tests whether or not the line has the <strong>Add to Inventory</strong> =
field set to true. This is used in organizations that have Inventory Manage=
r (Supplies Manager).</p>
<p>Example Activity:</p>
<p>&lt;Activity name=3D"Create Inventory"&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ActivityType&gt;automated&lt;/ActivityType&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;StepRef name=3D"Create Inventory Receipts"/&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;FolderRef name=3D"Create Inventory"/&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;Rule&gt;&lt;![CDATA[[DocLine.Replenishment=3Dtrue]]]&gt;&lt;/Rule&gt=
;</p>
<p>&lt;FolderSelectionRule&gt;ExplicitFolder&lt;/FolderSelectionRule&gt;</p=
>
<p>&lt;/Activity&gt;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>19.3</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span data-colorid=3D"lbqvbizoxv">[DocLine.Replenishment=3Dtrue]</span><=
/p>
<p>Use this in conjunction with a new robot called CreateInventoryRobot to =
route receipts to an activity that will generate inventory receipts for any=
 lines with the Add to Inventory field set to true.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">POQuantity</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Integer</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span>Returns the quantity of the =
PO line, not applicable for cost receipts.</span></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">20.1</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
